
1. What is Linear Regression in simple words?

Linear Regression models linear relationships between input features (X) and target variable (y) using:


y = β₀ + β₁X₁ + β₂X₂ + ... + βₙXₙ + ε

Optimization Objective: Minimize Mean Squared Error (MSE) via Ordinary Least Squares (OLS):


MSE = (1/n) × Σ(yᵢ - (β₀ + β₁X₁ᵢ + ... + βₙXₙᵢ))²

Production Implementation: sklearn.linear_model.LinearRegression.fit(X, y).



